## Listing Locations

> Example Request

```shell
curl <%=@api_prefix%>/locations \
 -H "W-Token: <%=@wiw_token%>"
```

> Example Response

```json
{
  "locations": [
    <%= print_json(data.objects['location'], :minimal=>true).indent(4) %>,
    <%= print_json(data.objects['location'], :minimal=>true, :include=>{'id'=>137,'name'=>'Uptown'}).indent(4) %>
  ]
}
```

### HTTP Request
`GET <%=@api_prefix%>/2/locations`



## Get Existing Location

> Example Request

```shell
curl <%=@api_prefix%>/locations/136 \
 -H "W-Token: <%=@wiw_token%>"
```

> Example Response

```json
{
  "location": <%= print_json(data.objects['location'], :minimal=>true).indent(2) %>
}
```

### HTTP Request
`GET <%=@api_prefix%>/2/locations/{id}`

### Parameters

Key | Description
--- | -----------
id | ID of the location requested.


## Create/Update Location

### Create HTTP Request
`POST <%=@api_prefix%>/2/locations/`

### Update HTTP Requests
`PUT <%=@api_prefix%>/2/locations/{id}`

### Parameters

The `POST` and/or `PUT` body can include fields from the [Location Object](#locations).

